<HEAD>Five Dead, 60 Injured in Mexican Gas Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas tank in a cafeteria exploded while it
was being filled in the western state of Michoacan, killing five
people and injuring 60, the government news agency Notimex reported
today.
   Notimex said the explosion occurred Wednesday in La Piedad, a
small town 210 miles northwest of Mexico City.
   The operator of the tank truck was killed instantly by the
blast, Notimex said. Other victims included four waiters in the
cafeteria and an unidentified woman. It said 60 people suffered
serious burns and cuts from flying glass shards.
   A spokesman for the state attorney general's office estimated
the damage at $8 million.
   Witnesses said window panes were shattered for blocks around by
the blast. Special guards had to be deployed at the entrance to two
nearby banks because their glass front doors were blown to bits.
