<SECOND>PM-Linkletter Hospitalized,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Art Linkletter Hospitalized with Chest Pains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Author and TV personality Art Linkletter was
reported in stable condition early today after being hospitalized
with chest pains.
   The 77-year-old humorist was taken by ambulance to the
University of California, Los Angeles, Medical Center on Wednesday
night and was undergoing observation and tests, said nursing
supervisor Susan Davidson.
   ``He is fully alert, talking and laughing,'' Ms. Davidson said.
   The cause of his chest pains was not immediately known, she said.
   The entertainer was stricken at his house less than a mile from
the home of former President Reagan and his wife, Nancy, in the
exclusive Bel Air area.
   Linkletter hosted several popular radio and TV shows, including
``Art Linkletter's House Party'' and ``People Are Funny.''
   His books ``Kids Say The Darndest Things'' and ``Old Age Is Not
For Sissies'' were best-sellers.
