<FIRST>u i PM-Salvador     08-10 0196</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Salvador,0202</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rebels Attack Post in Salvadoran Capital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist rebels today plowed
through a sentry position with a dump truck and attacked an army
post in the capital with grenades and automatic weapons,
authorities and witnesses said.
   Sgt. Arturo Melendez, who was commanding the Mejicanos post when
the rebels attacked at dawn, said one soldier and one civilian were
wounded.
   Another guerrilla squad ambushed a truck carrying National Guard
members to reinforce the Mejicanos post, killing one trooper and
wouding two, authorities said.
   Melendez told journalists about 30 insurgents fired
rocket-propelled grenades at the post in northern San Salvador and
sprayed it with automatic weapons fire.
   The attack began when several guerrillas aboard a dump truck
smashed through a roadblock serving as the post's perimeter. The
rebels also fired a grenades at the Mejicanos Town Hall, destroying
its door.
   Leftist rebels are waging a nearly 10-year-old revolution
against a series of U.S.-backed governments. The war has killed an
estimated 70,000 people, most of them civilians.
   At the weekend peace conference of Central American leaders in
Honduras, the five presidents signed an accord calling for peace
talks in El Salvador.
</TEXT>
