<FIRST>u a PM-EmergencyLanding     08-10 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Emergency Landing,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jetliner Develops Hydraulic Leak</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American Airlines airliner carrying 211
people from Phoenix to Chicago landed at Albuquerque International
Airport today after developing a hydraulic leak, officials said.
   The Boeing 767 landed about 9:40 a.m. with no loss of steering,
authorities said.
   ``The captain got an indicator that there was a loss of
hydraulic fluid, so he decided to land the plane in Albuquerque as
a precaution,'' said Ed Stewart, a spokesman for American Airlines
in Dallas.
   Ground crews found a valve near the wheel well had cracked and
caused a leak in one of the plane's three hydraulic systems, said
Don Ashmore general manager for American Airlines in Albuquerque.
   Hydraulic systems power brakes, flaps and other steering
surfaces.
</TEXT>
