<FIRST>u a PM-CoachShooting     08-10 0335</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Coach Shooting,0346</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coach Shoots Star and Kills Self on Freeway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOOMIS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A baseball coach described as obsessed
with his 16-year-old star pitcher shot her in front of several
motorists after she leaped from his moving pickup, then killed
himself, authorities said.
   The teen-ager, Suzanne Jacobs of North Highlands, was listed in
critical but stable condition today at the University Medical
Center in Sacramento.
   Sheriff's department spokeswoman Patti Davis said Jesse Aguilar,
42, of North Highlands shot the girl about 5 p.m. Tuesday on an
interstate highway as horrified witnesses who had stopped to help
the girl looked on.
   Motorists said they saw the girl open the passenger door and
jump out.
   A sheriff's deputy who stopped to help was giving the girl first
aid when the coach made his way through the onlookers and pulled a
large-caliber handgun, shot the girl behind the ear, then shot
himself in the head, authorities said.
   The motive for the attack was not immediately known. It was not
known where the coach and teen-ager were headed, sheriff's deputies
said.
   In 1985, Jacobs and Aguilar were featured on Sacramento
television because she was the only girl on her team and also the
star of the youth league.
   Her father, Roger Jacobs, said Aguilar was obsessed with her,
but he said there was no indication of a sexual relationship. He
said Aguilar had followed his daughter around and had tried to
obtain the address of a girl with whom his daughter had recently
become friends.
   Sheriff's Detective Bill Summers said, ``We know that they were
quite close, that they occasionally had their spats and mostly they
were about baseball. If there were other things in there, I really
don't know about it.''
   Jacobs said Aguilar had been his daughter's coach for six years.
He said she had had no social life except for the team, her coach
and his family, until this summer when she had gotten a job and
become friends with the other girl.
</TEXT>
