<SECOND>AM-Denitch-Heart,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Political Leader Suffers Heart Attack in Yugoslavia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bogdan Denitch, a leader of the
Democratic Socialists of America, suffered a heart attack while
vacationing in Yugoslavia but said Thursday he is recovering and
will be back in New York next month.
   He will be on hand for a Sept. 15 memorial for party chairman
Michael Harrington, who died on Aug. 2, the 60-year-old Denitch
told The Associated Press, which reached him by phone in a hospital
in the Adriatic port of Split.
   The Belgrade-born Denitch, who had a triple by-pass heart
operation in New York in 1983, said he suffered the heart attack on
Aug. 4.
   He teaches sociology and politics at the City University of New
York.
   Denitch is on the Executive Committee of the Democratic
Socialists of America and represents his party in the Socialist
International.
</TEXT>
