<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProdn     08-10 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
184,392 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
156,976, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 167,291 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 108,204 cars this week,
compared with 84,752 a week ago and 97,758 in the same week in 1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 76,188,
compared with last week's 72,224 and last year's 69,533.
   Canadian automakers were to build 11,401 cars this week, down
from 12,594 a week ago and from last year's 12,142.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 11,527,
compared with 9,233 a week ago and 17,089 in the same week last
year.
