<SECOND>AM-Texaco,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Texaco Ups Exploration In Argentina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Texaco Inc. said Thursday it has
increased its exploration interests in Argentina to more than 19
million acres.
   Texaco said its subsidiary in Argentina, Texaco Petrolera
Argentina S.A., has entered into nine new exploration contracts
with Argentina's state oil company, Yacimientos Petroliferos
Fiscales.
   Texaco, which has done business in Argentina since 1922, said it
expects to complete the contracts by next Monday.
   The nine contracts were awarded to Texaco as part of the
``Houston Plan,'' a program by Argentina's state oil company
started in 1985 to open the country's petroleum industry to private
investment.
