<FIRST>r f AM-Register-MailSale     08-10 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Register-Mail Sale,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>Journal Star Seeks Dismissal of Thompson Lawsuit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GALESBURG, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Attorneys for the Journal Star of Peoria
have asked the Knox County Circuit Court to dismiss a $40 million
lawsuit againt the newspaper brought by Thomson Newspapers.
   Thomson, a Toronto-based company that owns 157 daily newspapers
in North America, filed the lawsuit last month, accusing the
Journal Star of interfering with its contract to buy the Galesburg
Register-Mail and two weekly papers for $14.7 million. The deal
included an additional payment of $1.5 million to selected trustees.
   The Journal Star offered $15 million to buy the Register-Mail
and turn it into an employee-owned paper. It also bid $16 million
to buy the paper outright.
   U.S. District Judge Michael Mihm halted the sale to Thomson on
June 30 after former Register-Mail publisher John Pritchard and the
Journal Star sought an injunction. They contended Register-Mail
trustees had violated their fiduciary responsibilities as trustees
by accepting the Thomson offer.
   Thomson has appealed the injunction to the 7th U.S. Circuit
Court of Appeals in Chicago.
   In its request Wednesday, the Journal Star asked the Knox County
Court to dismiss Thompson's lawsuit because of the pending federal
cases.
</TEXT>
